19/10/2017 - Modification - Event 3772033$N***********************************************************$NThis modification has been carried out to silence all Brightness Meter alarms at the PCI only.$NThe PCI alarms will still occur and be:$N- indicated on the PCI alarms line and determine object status colour$N- be acted on as permissives to the Coal Valve and N2 Purge Valve for its associated line$N- be sent to BF5 to indicate to its control system of the alarm$Nbut they will no longer sound at PCI.$NAt this date only three alarms existed per brightness meter being: MIN (Wrng), MINMIN (Flt) and BrokenWire/SignalFault (Flt).$NThe mod. involves adding the flag below and ensuring that it is always OFF. This flag is then added in series with each of the 28 brightness meter AI_A5_2_5RTxx_FLT.HORN where it exists to set the HORN to ensure it will be disabled (xx refers to 01 thru to 28 for all brightness meters).

*******************************************************************************************************************$N*                                                                 DIGITAL INPUTS                                                          *$N*******************************************************************************************************************$N$NThis routine takes the real world raw digital inputs and places them into a buffered flag once per program scan. The buffered flag is then used within the plc program to represent the digital input.$NItems to note are:$N- The inputs are buffered once per scan (ie syncronous to the scan) because the raw digital inputs are updated ASyncronuous to the scan.$N- If a digital input module is detected as faulty the buffered inputs for that card are written to zero (via the use of the MCR commands).$N (When the first MCR instruction is disabled (module fault) the controller executes the rungs in the MCR zone (between the two MCR instructions) and the rung-condition-in goes false for all the rungs in the MCR zone, regardless of input conditions thus writing the outputs to a zero)$N

*************************************************************************************$N*                         RACK 1 SLOT 3 - Digital Input Module                          *$N*************************************************************************************$N$N- If a digital input module is detected as faulty the buffered inputs for that card are written to zero (via the use of the MCR commands) That is all the rungs between this MCR and the next MCR rung will be disabled/written to zero..$N  $N

*************************************************************************************$N*                         RACK 1 SLOT 5 - Digital Input Module                          *$N*************************************************************************************$N$N- If a digital input module is detected as faulty the buffered inputs for that card are written to zero (via the use of the MCR commands) That is all the rungs between this MCR and the next MCR rung will be disabled/written to zero..$N  $N
